<br>
Virtue, Focus of Souls, Stamina of the Boar, Spirit of Vigor ( Or Brell's if there's no Beastie near, I prefer SV 'cause of the attack... a handy ranger with Tunare's Strength is also perfectly acceptable :P ) And Primeval Aura... is nice too.<br>
<br>
Yes, you can get more hitpoint by either extensive kitty loving, druid hp buff / cleric symbol stacking etc, but that also clutters up your buff screen, and I'm happy as can be, when I have virtue, FoS, Sta, PA, SV, Acumen* and SoV. <br>
<br>
*Before you all start: I am human... it's nice to actually see... I wished there was an item with Acumen on it.. that didn't drop from the Emperor or such.... ah well.<br>
<br>
Those buffs put me at 7k hitpoints, with an ac of 1300+ and an attack of 1400+ (depending on the ranger/bst attention I get) which is my raid-norm. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=408912">Ygnir Thundersson</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
